'''Bocage's bushshrike''' ('''''Chlorophoneus bocagei'''''), also known as the '''grey-green bushshrike''', is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Malaconotidae]].  It is scatteredly present throughout central Africa.  Its natural [[habitat]]s are [[subtropical or tropical dry forest]] and [[subtropical or tropical moist lowland forest]].

